Compared to its more colorful neighbor, Bowery, Extra Place has left a slight historical imprint.
Some believe it took its name in 1802, when a large farm owned by Philip Minthorne was divided among his numerous sons and the narrow strip of land was not claimed.
The back door of CBGB, the punk rock monument that closed in 2006, opened on Extra Place, and the street is perhaps best known as the set for the cover photo of the Ramones' album "Rocket to Russia."
