Industry’s prices continue to rise
The prices of industrial domestic sales in August 2008 increased by 0.1% compared to the previous month, by 12.9% compared to August 2007 - reports the Central Institute of Hungarian Statistics.
The export sales prices of the industry in July 2008 were higher by 1.1%, compared to the previous year they decreased by 3.9%
As a result of the change in domestic and export prices, industrial production costs were 0.7% higher than the previous month and 3.2% higher than a year ago.
The prices of industrial domestic sales compared to the previous month increased by only 0.1%.
The prices of domestic sales in the processing sector also rose to a minimum of 0.1% compared to July.
The largest increase in prices in August 2008 occurred in the leather and shoes processing sector (2.8%), especially bags and belts with 4.6% and the production of shoes with a 2.5% monthly increase.
The high price level of plastics and chemicals has caused a significant monthly increase (1.6%) in the product and chemicals sector.
A decrease in prices occurred in the oil processing sector (1.4%), in the production of electric tools and machinery (0.9%) and to a minimum in the wood processing (0.1%)
The prices of paper production, editorial and typographical activities have not changed.
In the other sectors of the processing industry, prices increased between 0.2 and 0.9%.
In the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector, prices rose by 0.3% in August in industrial domestic sales, primarily as a result of the dominant effect of the rise in the price of gas carried out by the authorities since 1 July.
Compared to 12 months, considering the domestic sales of the processing industries, the largest increases were in the processing of petroleum products (32.4%).
In the manufacturing sector of products derived from the processing of metals, the increase in prices was 13.2%, of 11% in the production of food, beverages and tobacco representing a decisive weight.
There was a drop in prices in the textile sector (2.5%) and in the production of electric tools and machinery (0.3%).
In other sectors of the manufacturing industry, the rate of price increase varied from 0.6% to 9.1%.
In total in the manufacturing industry last year prices rose by 10.2%.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sector exceeded last year’s 18.7%.
In domestic sales among target groups of sectors, the largest increase in monthly prices occurred in August in the sectors producing investment goods (0.7%).
In the sectors that produce consumer goods, prices have increased by 0.3%, in the energy and after-use sector prices have not changed compared to the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month last year, the largest increase in prices was observed in the energy and subsequent use sector (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods, the increase was 6.8%, for investment goods a decrease of 1.4% was measured.
The prices of industrial export sales calculated in florals increased by 1.1% in August compared to the previous month, compared to 12 months, decreased by 3.9%.
The Hungarian florin in one month weakened against the euro by 1.7%, against the dollar by 7.1%, compared with August 2007 by 7.5% against the euro and by 15.9% against the dollar.
